snippet.textDisplay:
I haven't seen 1917 or Jumanji 3 yet. They probably would be on my top 10 list for 2019. --- Spoilers Below!


(Spoilers Below, in case you didn't see that in the previous line)


#10 Joker ---- solid origin story for the Joker. It makes sense. Super dark sense. It's what returning evil for evil looks like
#9 Alita Battle Angel ---- honors the manga very well, but so many important questions left unanswered
#8 Maleficent : Mistress of Evil ---- great scenarios touching on Maleficent's distrust of humans in power
#7 Escape Room ---- non stop action and I love the mental games this movie is jam packed with
#6 Spider-man : Far From Home ---- a good story about the origin of team Spider-man
#5 Shazam! ---- Full of fun and a total surprise that the Marvel Family was brought on board in the first Shazam movie
#4 The Rise of Skywalker ---- Chewie finally got a medal!!!!! Wonderful Space Soap Opera Craziness everywhere!
#3 Ford vs Ferrari ---- Has a great message : Strive for excellence even when your own team is against you
#2 Avengers : Endgame ---- Amazing reminder of how good the 10 year arc of Marvel stories is
#1 Toy Story 4 ---- Has a great answer to the question : What if the one you love rejects you?
